    "Here, yi,c uses a one-hot encoding of the actual class, pi,c refers to a matrix of predicted values for every class, and c, i refers to iterating over all classes and pixels.",
    "In this study, we employed binary cross-entropy, the most prevalent loss function for binary classification tasks.",
    "This section proposes an efficient breast cancer classification approach that integrates several pre-trained CNN models.",
